<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that Digikam supports <b>Drag'n'Drop</b>? So you could easily move images from Konqueror to Digikam or from Digikam to K3b simply by using "Drag'n'Drop".
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you could use the album collection feature go get your Photos sorted into two level? First, the collection; then, the album.
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that the Properties entry of each photo gives you access to the properties entry of Konqueror?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you could edit the <b>EXIF</b> Information of a photo by using its properties dialog?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that each photo has a context menu that can be reached by clicking on it with the right mouse button?
</html>
</tip>

<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you could use the keys <b>1</b>, <b>2</b>, and <b>3</b> for rotating your images?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that albums in Digikam are Folders in your Album Library? So you could easily import your Photos by simply copying them to your Album Library.
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you could customize your digikam toolbars using Settings -> Configure Toolbars...?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that Digikam registers itself as a <b>DCOP</b> Server? So you could write your own scripts automating Digikam.
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that there is a Digikam hotplugging howto available at
<a href="http://digikam.free.fr/hotplug/howto.html">http://digikam.free.fr/hotplug/howto.html</a> ?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you could reach other users and Digikam developers using the digikam-users mailinglist? Subscribe yourself to the list using <a href="https://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/digikam-users">https://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/digikam-users</a>.
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that Digikam has multiple Plugins with extra features like <b>HTML export</b>, <b>Archive to CD</b>, <b>Slideshow</b>,... and that you are welcome to write your own plugins? You can find more information about this at <a href="http://digikam.sourceforge.net/plugins.html">http://digikam.sourceforge.net/plugins.html</a>.
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you have direct access to the KDE Gamma Configuration using Tools -> Gamma Settings -> KDE Gamma Configuration ?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you could print images using the Print Wizard? You can start it using Image -> Print Wizard.
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|ImageViewer">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you could use <Page Down> and <Page Up> on your Keyboard to switch between the photos in the image viewer?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you can use <b>PNG</b> file format instead of <b>TIFF</b> for good compression without losing image quality?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that the all options in a dialog box have <b>What's this?</b> information available with the right mouse button?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you could brighten up your images using Tools -> Batch -> Color Images -> Increase Contrast?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you can use the Digikam plugins with the showimg program (<a href="http://www.jalix.org/projects/showimg/">http://www.jalix.org/projects/showimg/</a>) ?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that because PNG file format use a no lossless compression algorithm, you can use the max compression level with this file format ?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|ImageViewer">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you can print the current image opened in the Digikam imageViewer with the 
contextual menu?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|ImageViewer">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you can edit the comments of the current image opened in the Digikam imageViewer with 
the contextual menu?
</html>
</tip>
